==Competitive record==
The best result Switzerland have achieved thus far is the quarter-finals of the [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] on three occasions, in [[1934 FIFA World Cup|1934]], [[1938 FIFA World Cup|1938]] and [[1954 FIFA World Cup|1954]], while they also reached the same stage at [[UEFA Euro 2020|Euro 2020]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024|2024]]. They earned a silver medal at the [[1924 Summer Olympics|1924 Olympic Games]], held in [[Paris]], where they lost 3–0 to [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] in the [[Football at the 1924 Summer Olympics#Gold medal match|final]]. This edition along with the 1928 are considered by FIFA as World Cup finals<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/mensolympic/paris1924/matches/round=197028/match=32314/index.html|title=Olympic Football Tournament Paris 1924 - Switzerland 0:3 (0:1) Uruguay - Overview|website=FIFA|access-date=5 July 2018}}</ref>

